OL,3,C'They sold me a dream': Botched Turkey
OL,4,Csurgery patients left with 'no support'
OL,6,FChristian went back to the clinic
OL,7,Fwhere he'd had the work done. They
OL,8,Ftold him his symptoms were normal, and
OL,9,Fthen they ghosted him - even blocking
OL,10,Fhis attempts to communicate with them
OL,11,Fon social media.
OL,13,F"They sold me a dream," he said.
OL,15,F"But there was no support, it was
OL,16,Fjust, 'see you later'. That was it."
OL,18,FChristian ended up having corrective
OL,19,Fsurgery with another surgeon in
OL,20,FTurkey. He reckons the whole process
OL,21,Fcost him somewhere around #20,000.
